description: The lncRNA bdnf-as is related to many neurological disorders,including huntington's disease (hd),schizophrenia,and depression.

The disruption of the disc genomic locus,which encodes both the disc1 protein-coding gene and the disc2 lncRNA,has been linked in a number of genetic analyses to the risk of developing schizophrenia,schizophrenia,bipolar disorder,major depression,and autistic spectrum disorders.
